    <div id="School-Day" class="content-section">
      <h1>Day Routine</h1>
      <p>Learn about our daily schedule and engaging activities for Pre-Nursery children.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Arrival & Welcome:</strong> 7:30am – 8:00am. Children are welcomed with stories and warm routines.</li>
        <li><strong>Circle Time:</strong> 8:00am – 8:30am. Music, movement, and sharing help build listening and social skills.</li>
        <li><strong>Activity Stations:</strong> 8:30am – 10:00am. Learning centers for art, language, early math, and sensory play.</li>
        <li><strong>Snack & Outdoor Play:</strong> 10:00am – 10:45am. Healthy snacks and playground time for energy release and social interaction.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Learning:</strong> 10:45am – 12:00pm. Hands-on projects, story-based learning, and imaginative play.</li>
        <li><strong>Lunch & Rest:</strong> 12:00pm – 1:30pm. Nutritious meals followed by quiet rest and relaxed activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Afternoon Learning:</strong> 1:30pm – 2:30pm. Group games, guided play, and reflection on the day.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick-Up:</strong> 2:30pm – 3:00pm. Children leave with updates for parents and a calm transition home.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/successful-schoolgirl_1098-13593.avif" alt="Pre-Nursery Activities" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
    </div>

    <div id="Curriculum" class="content-section">
      <h1>Curriculum</h1>
      <p>Discover our Pre-Nursery curriculum created for young learners ready to build confidence and curiosity.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language & Literacy:</strong> Songs, stories, and vocabulary activities that strengthen speaking and listening.</li>
        <li><strong>Numeracy:</strong> Number play, shapes, and pattern exploration through hands-on games.</li>
        <li><strong>Science & Discovery:</strong> Simple investigations, sensory play, and nature discovery to spark wonder.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Arts:</strong> Drawing, painting, dance, and craft projects to develop imagination.</li>
        <li><strong>Social & Emotional Learning:</strong> Turn-taking, sharing, empathy, and self-awareness in a caring community.</li>
        <li><strong>Faith & Values:</strong> Christian morals, kindness, and character-building through daily routines.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/other-uniform.webp" alt="Pre-Nursery Curriculum" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
    </div>

    <div id="Frequently-Asked-Questions" class="content-section">
      <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p>Find answers to common questions about our Pre-Nursery program.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>What are the age requirements?</strong> Our Pre-Nursery program is designed for children aged 2 to 4 years old.</li>
        <li><strong>What is the teacher-to-child ratio?</strong> We maintain a low ratio of 1:8 to ensure personalized attention and a strong sense of belonging.</li>
        <li><strong>What safety measures are in place?</strong> Our classrooms are secure, with trained staff, safe play areas, and regular health protocols.</li>
        <li><strong>How do you handle meals and allergies?</strong> We provide healthy snacks and accommodate dietary needs with active communication and supervision.</li>
        <li><strong>Can parents visit the classroom?</strong> Yes, we encourage parent involvement with scheduled observations and regular feedback.</li>
      </ul>
      <img src="/images/people/other-uniform.webp" alt="Pre-Nursery FAQ" style="max-width: 100%; margin-top: 1em; border-radius: 8px;" loading="lazy">
